description.plain:
Denzel Rae Don Curry, formally known as Denzel Curry, was born in Carol City, Florida on February 16, 1995. He is of Bahamian and Native American descent.

He started rapping in 6th grade and frequently challenged others to rap battles at a local Boys & Girls club. He attended Miami’s Design And Architecture High School for his first two years of high school before being expelled. He went on to attend Carol City High School while he worked on what would become his debut album, Nostalgic 64.

Throughout 2011-2012, he posted various amateur mixtapes on SoundCloud and DatPiff such as King Remembered in 2011 and Strictly For my R.V.I.D.X.R.Z in 2012, which grabbed the attention of Earl Sweatshirt.

Not long after the group disbanded, he joined SpaceGhostPurrp’s group Raider Klan. After several disagreements between Purrp and Denzel, he would leave the group and, simultaneously, start his solo rap career, alongside the release of his SpaceGhostPurrp’s 2016 diss-track, “PURRPOSELY.”

His debut album Nostalgic 64 was released in September 2013, and was followed by a double-sided EP in June 2015 titled 32 Zel/Planet Shrooms, which included the gold-certified and breakout hit single, “ULTIMATE.”

His last release before a hiatus was his second studio album/mixtape hybrid, Imperial, which was released in March 2016.

On July 17, Denzel released his critically acclaimed third studio album, TA13OO, which was divided into three acts, released period 3 days of the complete album: “Light,” released on July 15; “Gray,” released on July 16; and “Dark,” released on July 17, alongside the entire album — After its release, it became his first charting album worldwide, peaking at #28 on the Billboard 200, and received generally positive reviews.

Almost a year after releasing the project, on May 31, 2019, Curry dropped his fourth studio album, ZUU, dedicated to his life in Carol City and inspired by the Miami culture, including features from Rick Ross, Kiddo Marv, Sam Sneak or Ice Billion Berg, the album has two supporting singles, his gold-certified single “RICKY” and “SPEEDBOAT.”

On February 7, 2020, Denzel would team up with his frequent collaborator and friend, Kenny Beats to release their collaborative 8-track project, UNLOCKED, and exactly one year later, on March 5, 2021, UNLOCKED 1.5, a re-edition of the project was released.

Nearly three years later after his latest album, on March 25, 2022, Denzel released what would be his evolution musically than he usually has, with his fifth studio album, Melt My Eyez, See Your Future — The 14-track album would have 3 promotional singles during its rollout: “Walkin,” “Zatoichi” with slowthai, and “Troubles” with veteran rapper T-Pain.

songs.lyrics:
95 ContributorsTranslationsEspañolSvenskaMelt Session #1 Lyrics
Yo

Take a ride on my train of thought, fundamentals what I bought
Penniless, I await the emptiness enlightened
Twenty-six years on Earth, my soul fighting
Habits that ain't happen, my body has took a liken
To my lifestyle, battling stress the size of Goliath
Slingshots plus hard rocks, these stones getting thrown
My temptations are amplified when I get alone
Tried to separate the action from the man
I wholeheartedly understand why I need to grow even though I'm grown
If I did you wrong, I vow to make it right
Judgе me off appearance, it was said to mе, I'm impolite
Eyes remain in freeze mode, I'm stuck in fight-or-flight
I'm deflecting my daily problems within my daily life
Recognize hidden patterns of my own demise
Why I feel like hiding a truth is finding a lie?
Dealt with thoughts of suicide, women I've objectified
Couldn't see it through my eyes so for that, I apologize
I'm just hypnotized, working hard to empathize
Strung out on love addiction and groupies when souls collide
I've been this way since the day I turned six
I've been touched before, way before I touched my—
Now I'm almighty pushing through the pain
The almighty cushion to the flame
The birds and burning bushes in my brain
I had to make an effort, double overtime to change
Had to journal my journey and mistakes I made on the way
Manipulation to get what I want
Getting very distant after I got what I need
Writing rap and wisdom, whiskey, women, wars and weed
Narrating all these conflicts, then top it off with greed
I keep walkin', I keep walkin', I keep walkin'
Me and my so-called best friends don't speak often
Blaming me for everything when they can't point fingers at they selves, so be grateful I offered the help
Being aware is my definition of melt
My eyes see imperfections within myself
Cracked images, bad luck, and broken mirrors
Funny how I see in permanent so clearer
I dedicate this to the ones I hurt
It's time to get my spirit right on earth
Before my sins become a evil curse
Conquer thirst, can't revert to who I was at first
I channel God through this verse
Accountability, I take responsibility
For all my actions, I packed them in these soliloquies
Just because we're not friends don't mean we're enemies
Thank you all for listening, sending y'all with good energy
